            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let’s get started!</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Trim, then chop your <strong>green beans </strong>in half</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1705677605359-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1705677605359-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1705677605359-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1705677605359-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1705677605359-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add your <strong>pork mince </strong>(remove the paper if required!) and <strong>chopped green beans </strong>to the pan and cook for 3-4 min, breaking the mince up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1705677612227-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1705677612227-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1705677612227-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1705677612227-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1705677612227-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Squeeze the pouch[es] of <strong>cooked white long grain rice </strong>to separate the grains</p><p>Tear the top corner of the pouch[es] ( just a little!) and <strong>microwave </strong>for 2 min or until piping hot</p><p>Tip: If you’re cooking two packets, pop them in together but increase the microwave cook time accordingly</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-1705677621669-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-1705677621669-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-copy-1705677621669-x700.jpg",
